            . I apprehended the prisoner on the 21st of March, about nine o'clock, on another charge; I found in his pocket the duplicate of the umbrella.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in Oxford-street, and met a man with this umbrella and a saw - he asked me to buy them, I said I had not much money - he said</p>
               <p>"Let us go and get something to drink," we did so, and then I went and pawned the things and came back - we had a pot or two more.</p>
